The paper deals with the stretch factor of the Yao graph, which is a geometric graph used in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the properties of the graph, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The lower bound on the stretch factor involves numerical analysis, which is related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the Yao-Yao graph, which is a variant of the Yao graph, and its properties, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
